cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AI. 

The paper deals with blind channel estimation, modulation classification, and data detection, which are all related to information theory and communication systems. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed approach for both single and multiple receivers, which falls under the category of networked systems, making cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) a likely sub-category as well. The proposed approach involves recognizing the unknown modulation and coding scheme, which can be seen as a classification problem, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a complete blind receiver approach that jointly estimates the unknown channel state information and noise power, which can be seen as a machine learning problem, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category.
